Interface BinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of data stored in this BinarySearchTree
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    public interface BinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>

    A BinarySearchTree is a container that maintains an internal state consistent with a Binary Search Tree.

    Author:
    jddevaug

    • Method Detail

      • add

        BinarySearchTree<T> add​(T toAdd)
        Adds toAdd to this BinarySearchTree. For convenience, this method returns the modified BinarySearchTree. This method runs in O(size) time. However, if this BinarySearchTree is balanced, this method runs in O(log(size)) time. A successful call to this method will always result in size increasing by one.
        Parameters:
        toAdd - the element to add to this BinarySearchTree
        Returns:
        For convenience, this method returns the modified BinarySearchTree.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if toAdd is null

      • contains

        boolean contains​(T toFind)
        Searches this BinarySearchTree for toFind and returns true if there is at least one instance of toFind in this BinarySearchTree and false otherwise. This method runs in O(size) time. However, if this BinarySearchTree is balanced, this method runs in O(log(size)) time.
        Parameters:
        toFind - the element to search for
        Returns:
        true if there is an instance of toFind in this BinarySearchTree and {@code false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if toFind is null

      • remove

        boolean remove​(T toRemove)
        Removes toRemove from this BinarySearchTree if at least one element is considered comparably equivalent (compareTo(toRemove) == 0). Returns true if this BinarySearchTree was modified and false otherwise. This method runs in O(size) time. However, if this BinarySearchTree is balanced, this method runs in O(log(size)) time.
        Parameters:
        toRemove - the element to be removed
        Returns:
        true if this BinarySearchTree was modified and false otherwise

      • toBinaryTreeNode

        BinaryTreeNode<T> toBinaryTreeNode()
        Returns a BinaryTreeNode that is consistent with the internal shape of this BinarySearchTree. If changes to the this BinarySearchTree are made after a call to this method, using the returned BinaryTreeNode is undefined.
        Returns:
        a BinaryTreeNode that is consistent with the shape of this BinarySearchTree.
        Throws:

      • iterator

        java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()

        Returns a new Iterator that will traverse this tree in-order.

        The remove method of the returned Iterator is not supported and any call to it will result in an UnsupportedOperationException.

        This method is guaranteed to return in O(1) time. That is, it should not compute the entire order of traversal ahead of time.

        If the data in the underlying BinaryTreeNode or its children is modified, using the Iterator is unknown.

        Specified by:
        iterator in interface java.lang.Iterable<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
        Returns:
        a new Iterator that will traverse this tree in-order.
